LAGOS  – Global Property Partners, a member of Cavalli Business and Investment Group, which specialises in the acquisition, development and management of retail, commercial, industrial and mixed-use properties have concluded plans to showcase many opportunities inherent in the United Kingdom property market to Nigerians. Mohammed Abdullahi, its Media Consultant in a statement, stated that the arrays of property experts would unveil these in its scheduled zoom webinar meeting slated for Thursday, April 28, 2022. The virtual meeting is with the theme: ‘The UK Advantage: Economic Prospects, Real Estate and Trust.’ The statement hinted that the property experts from Nigeria and the United Kingdom have been confirmed to educate Nigerians and corporate bodies on the advantages of investing in the property market in the Queen’s land. The webinar, the statement emphasised was aimed at laying bare the acceptable professional and legal processes of investing and acquiring properties of all kinds in the United Kingdom. Emmanuel Odemayowa, Chief Executive Officer of Global Property Partners and the host of the event, speakers including Sam Philip, Global Sales Director and Jennifer Lawler, Partnership Manager both of SalBoy United Kingdom, a leading property developing firm have been confirmed. Azeem Khan, Chief Executive Officer of GulfCoast Finance United Arab Emirates and United Kingdom is also confirmed speaker, the statement stated. Odemayowa stated that Global Property Partners understood the trends and dynamics of the continuous growth in Nigeria middle class yearning for upscale and luxury properties both in Nigeria and abroad. POLL He said: “The investment rationale of owning luxury real estate remains attractive and has continued to grow in Nigeria and among Nigerians. This growing trend is our driving force in showcasing global property investment opportunities to Nigerian individuals and corporates in acquiring short and long term secured assets.”